-- 
Greek Review to Look at Reducing Labor Costs, Kathimerini Says

-- B y   M a r c u s   B e n s a s s o n
-- 
2011-12-12T08:52:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-12/greek-review-to-look-at-reducing-labor-costs-kathimerini-says.html
The European Commission,  European
Central Bank  and  International Monetary Fund  will press  Greece 
to cut labor costs at private businesses,  Kathimerini  reported,
without saying where it got the information.  Inspectors from the three agencies begin a review of
Greece today and will suggest measures, including reducing
holiday bonus payments and canceling wage increases agreed on
under a 2010 collective labor agreement, the Athens-based
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marcus Bensasson in Athens at 
 mbensasson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at 
 cstirling1@bloomberg.net  